<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code passes file->cfg->attrs[i].buffer and a size derived from file->cfg->attrs[i].size into lfs_dir_get (which calls lfs_dir_getslice and eventually memory-copy routines). There is no check here that the buffer actually has at least file->cfg->attrs[i].size bytes (the code only checks attrs[i].size <= lfs->attr_max for the write-path, not for the read-path). If a caller provides a lfs_file_config with attrs[i].buffer smaller than attrs[i].size, lfs_dir_getslice/memcpy would write past the end of the buffer, causing an out‑of‑bounds access via the C library memory functions. Therefore the rule can be violated in this scenario.
</scenario>

